				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You need to make an NMI routine, and have the NSF Play routine called from there.  Use JSR, rather than JMP.
<br />
<br />For the init routine, load the song # into A and JSR to the init routine.  Some players will use the X or Y register to select NTSC or PAL.  After that point you can enable NMI, then do whatever in your main loop while the play routine runs automatically.  You need to disable NMI or otherwise stop playing when you change tracks.
<br />
<br />With 2 Nintendos you could take 2 NES controller cables, link them and cross-wire the D0 and strobe/latch lines for communication.  That'd be a fancy way to make it sync up, but with the right software in place, you wouldn't have to change the EPROM.  That would require a custom sound engine though.</div>

