						<div class="postbody">You could hook one controller to 2 NES's, but you will need to add a 2nd CD4021 chip in there.  If there's enough room, ideally it could piggy-back on top of the original to simplify the connections.  For the 2nd chip, then you would bend up the pins used for clk and data, which would go only to the 2nd cable.</div>

